Avatar has a fallback (initials). Long name is truncated. Long URL breaks naturally. Nothing breaks the layout.

## Murphy's Law for UIs

- Always design for the worst-case user content.
- Use truncation, max-widths, and word-breaking.
- Create fallback states for missing content.
- Test with real user data, not perfect samples.
